<1ST_LINE>r a PM-BabyKilled     08-22 0204</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Baby Killed,0212</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Van Kills Baby; Driver Beaten by Mob</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A drunken driver was beaten and seriously
injured by a mob after his van struck a mother pushing a baby
carriage in a park, killing her 4-month-old son, police said.
   The driver, Lorgio Cano, was in critical but stable condition
this morning at Jacobi Hospital, said Cynthia Balot, a nursing
supervisor. He suffered severe head trauma, said police Lt. Edward
Shalvey.
   Cano, 59, was charged with manslaughter, driving while
intoxicated and other violations of traffic and park regulations,
Shalvey said.
   The crash occurred Sunday evening at a soccer field in Van
Cortlandt Park in the Bronx, said Sgt. John Venetucci, a police
spokesman.
   Cano was leaving the area with his family after watching a
soccer game when his van struck the carriage pushed by Luisa
Martinez, 21.
   She was treated at a hospital for minor injuries; her son,
Justo, was pronounced dead at North Central Bronx Hospital, police
said.
   After the crash, a large crowd set upon the van, beating Cano,
his wife and children, Shalvey said. Cano's relatives received
minor injuries, Shalvey said.
   Eight people were treated for minor injuries, said Capt. Donald
Rothschild of Emergency Medical Services.
