<HEAD>Dollar Gains, Stocks Fall in Japanese Trading</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: UPDATES with morning closing Nikkei, dollar</NOTE>
<DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Stock prices fell on the Tokyo Stock Exchange
Monday, while the dollar edged up.
   The Nikkei Stock Average of 225 selected issues, a 80.06-point
winner Friday, lost 130.24 points, or 0.46 percent, to close at
28,079.18.
   The dollar closed at 133.88 yen, up 0.48 yen from the last
week's close after moving between 133.80 yen and 133.95 yen.
   Trading was moderate on the stock exchange's first section, with
volume at 600 million shares.
   Exchange dealers said the yen-dollar rate was not likely to
change much for the moment because if the U.S. currency touches the
134-yen level, investors are likely to sell the dollar.
