in a motorized hang glider Monday and asked for political asylum,
authorities said.
   Gabor Loerinczy, showed up at the police station at
Grosspetersdorf, about five miles west of the Hungarian border,
according to police and the Interior Ministry.
   Loerinczy, 36, arrived at the police station on foot and said he
had made an emergency landing in a forest because of engine
trouble, a spokesman for the ministry said. He said he lived in
Gyula, a Hungarian town on the Romanian border.
