been waiting for a decision on their appeal for asylum for about a
year, the ministry spokesman said.
   He added it was not known why Loerinczy was seeking asylum.
   Austria and Hungary have abolished visa requirements for their
citizens, and liberalized Hungarian travel laws allow Hungarians to
travel to the West as often as they can afford to, provided they
are granted a passport. Most Hungarians who apply are granted
passports.
