<HEAD>Memorial Service Planned At Fort Campbell For Victim Of Pakistan
Crash</HEAD>
<DATELINE>FORT CAMPBELL, Ky. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A public memorial service will be held
Thursday at Fort Campbell for Brig. Gen. Herbert M. Wassom, killed
in the plane crash that also killed Pakistan President Mohammed Zia
Ul-Haq, the Army said Monday.
   Wassom left Fort Campbell in July 1987 to assume his post as
chief U.S. defense representative to Pakistan.
   Wassom's last position at Fort Campbell was assistant commander
of the 101st Airborne Division.
   Wassom, 49, is to be buried at Arlington National Cemetery
outside Washington with full military honors.
   Also killed in last week's plane crash was U.S. Ambassador
Arnold L. Raphel.
   A statement issued by the military base said a scholarship fund
in Wassom's name has been established for Western Kentucky
University, where Wassom graduated in 1961.
