<1ST_LINE>r a AM-BabyKilled     08-22 0288</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Baby Killed,0295</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Mob Attacks Alleged Drunken Driver Who Killed Infant</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Witnesses who saw a van run over a 4-month-old
boy in a park attacked the driver, his wife and children,
authorities said.
   Lorgio Cano, 59, who was charged with second-degree
manslaughter, driving while intoxicated, driving without a license
and driving in an unauthorized area, was reported in satisfactory
condition Monday at a hospital where he was being treated for
severe head trauma.
   Sgt. John Venetucci said the incident occurred shortly after a
soccer match Sunday night in Van Cortlandt Park in the borough of
the Bronx.
   Venetucci said Cano; his wife, Blanca; and their five children,
ages 4 to 14, got into the family van which was illegally parked on
the edge of the playing field.
   He started driving across the field when he apparently lost
control and struck a baby carriage being pushed by Louisa Martinez,
21, Venetucci said. Mrs. Martinez's 4-month-old son, Justo, was
killed.
   A crowd ran to the van and yanked Cano and his family from the
vehicle.
   ``They were hitting all of them with rocks and sticks _ even the
children,'' said Emergency Medical Service specialist Michael Mohn.
``When we tried to get to them to treat them (the Canos) the crowd
started screaming at us. They wanted to keep us away from them.''
   Mohn said he and his partner, John Ortiz, had to fight their way
through the crowd and fight their way back to the ambulance with
the injured Cano.
   The rest of the Cano family and two others believed to have been
involved in the fight were treated for minor injuries. Mrs.
Martinez suffered a minor leg injury and was also treated and
released.
</TEXT>
