<HEAD>Bomb Kills One Person In East Belfast</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BELFAST, Northern Ireland (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A bomb blew up a car in east
Belfast on Monday afternoon, killing one person, police said.
   It was not immediately known whether the victim was a civilian
or a member of the security forces in the British province, a
spokesman for the Royal Ulster Constabulary said.
   The device went off in heavy traffic during rush hour, but first
reports indicated the person in the car was the only casualty, the
spokesman said. He spoke on condition of anonymity, in keeping with
British practice.
   There was no immediate claim of responsibility for the bombing.
   On Friday, an Irish Republican Army bomb killed eight British
soldiers in Northern Ireland. The outlawed IRA has targeted
security forces in its fight to drive the British out of the
province and unite it with the Irish Republic.
