<HEAD>As Many As 400 at Jail Have Strep; All Inmates Are Treated</HEAD>
<DATELINE>EAST MEADOW, N.Y. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Health officials are trying to track
down the source of a strep throat epidemic that has stricken about
400 inmates and 13 employees at the county jail.
   Nassau County Health Department officials began collecting air
samples and taking nose and throat cultures of kitchen workers at
the East Meadow facility.
   The entire jail population, including almost 1,500 inmates and
800 staff personnel, was put on antibiotics in an attempt to stem
the outbreak.
   ``Everyone, even me, is on pills,'' said Sheriff Joseph
Jablonsky. ``It's been very disruptive, to say the least.''
   Jablonsky canceled all court appearances by inmates until
Tuesday. He also canceled jail visits and outside volunteer work.
