<HEAD>Police Arrest Suspect in 60 Rapes</HEAD>
<DATELINE>COLUMBUS, Ohio (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A suspect in a four-year string of attacks
attributed to the ``handcuff rapist'' faces charges in as many as
60 rapes, police say.
   Robert Biddings, 34, of Columbus, was arrested Friday and was
being held in the Franklin County jail on a single rape count.
   Police spokeswoman Denise Pangborn said Biddings is a suspect in
a series of attacks dating to 1984 and attributed a person
nicknamed because he used handcuffs in early attacks.
