<HEAD>Soviets Detonate Nuclear Device</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MOSCOW (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Soviet Union detonated a nuclear device in the
Tyumen region of Siberia on Monday, the Tass news agency reported.
   Tass said the underground blast had a yield of up to 20,000 tons
of TNT, and was ``made in the interests of the national economy.''
   It gave no further information.
   In addition to making tests of its nuclear weaponry, the Soviet
Union sometimes uses nuclear devices underground to loosen mineral
deposits.
   The Tyumen region is one of the Soviet Union's most important
oil and natural gas regions.
