<TEXT>
   The League of Women Voters said Monday it
expects an estimated 15,000 phone calls to flood the campaign
headquarters of George Bush and Michael Dukakis pushing the 1988
presidential and vice presidential nominees to take part in
League-sponsored debates this fall.
