<HEAD>Presort Stamp to Feature Fire Engine</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An antique fire engine will be featured on the
latest stamp in the U.S. Postal Service's transportation series,
the agency reported today.
   The 20.5-cent stamp will be used for first class mail,
pre-sorted by ZIP code.
   Featured on the stamp is a 1913 Ahrens-Fox fire engine, which
was sold to San Angelo, Texas. San Angelo will be the site of the
first day of issue ceremonies for the new stamp, scheduled for
Sept. 28.
