<HEAD>Batus Extends Offer Deadline</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOUISVILLE, Ky. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Batus Inc. has extended to Wednesday its
$72 per share cash offer for Farmers Group Inc., one of the
nation's largest insurers, the companies announced Monday.
   The deadline had been scheduled to expire last Friday.
   In a statement Monday, Batus also reported that negotiations
between it and the Los Angeles-based company were ``progressing
satisfactorily,'' but said there would be no comment from either
side about the talks.
   Farmers and Batus, based in Louisville, have been battling
before insurance regulators in nine states where the merger
proposal must be approved.
   Arizona regulators have approved the deal, and Illinois and Ohio
officials have given tentative approval, imposing conditions that
Batus has said it would meet.
   Idaho, Washington and Oregon have rejected a merger, and
decisions or hearings are pending in Texas and Kansas. California
regulators turned down the deal, but that decision was overturned
by a court.
   In the various insurance hearings, Farmers has argued that
Batus' tobacco interests would make the company reluctant to
continue the insurer's emphasis on non-smoker discounts.
   Batus has promised to continue the discounts if a merger is
approved. Batus is the U.S. management arm for London-based B.A.T.
Industries PLC.
