development which might normally support stock prices.
   But the pace of economic growth has raised concerns about a
resurgence of inflation and speculation that the Federal Reserve
may take new steps to choke off a price rise by pushing interest
rates higher.
   Higher rates would make the yields available on bonds more
attractive.
