for compensation of the public in the event of an accident.
   The bill signed Monday extends for 15 years a law passed in the
1970s designed to provide such protection.
   The new law, like the old one, requires private insurance of
$150 million per reactor. It increases from $5 million to $63
million per reactor the second-tier insurance, provided by the
federal government.
